WEBVTT

00:01.349 --> 00:03.220
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYS]

00:03.264 --> 00:06.049
[SHOVEL SCRAPING]

00:06.093 --> 00:09.052
♪♪

00:18.670 --> 00:21.412
[BIRDS SQUAWK]

00:24.067 --> 00:25.895
[WIND WHISTLING]

00:42.738 --> 00:45.262
[PLANE ENGINE RUNNING]

00:51.573 --> 00:52.965
JESSE: All right?

00:54.402 --> 00:56.708
Now it's your turn.

00:56.752 --> 00:58.971
Just pick a spot.

01:00.016 --> 01:01.670
And put it
in your mind's eye.

01:01.713 --> 01:03.280
You got it?

01:05.195 --> 01:06.718
Now let it fly.

01:11.549 --> 01:12.594
[CHUCKLES]

01:12.637 --> 01:14.509
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

01:14.552 --> 01:17.120
♪♪

01:22.343 --> 01:23.474
Hello.

01:35.747 --> 01:36.922
Who am I?

01:37.575 --> 01:38.315
Fiore.

01:38.968 --> 01:40.143
Who are you?

01:40.187 --> 01:42.058
Jesse Custer.

01:42.102 --> 01:43.364
Right. Good.

01:44.408 --> 01:45.105
Am I dead?

01:45.801 --> 01:47.107
Yeah.

01:47.977 --> 01:50.414
[DUCK QUACKS]

01:50.458 --> 01:52.155
This is Heaven?

01:52.199 --> 01:55.027
Well, it ain't
the South of France.

01:55.811 --> 01:57.117
Who is that?

02:00.032 --> 02:02.426
I don't know.
Some girl fishing.

02:02.470 --> 02:04.167
Come on.

02:07.649 --> 02:09.433
JESSE: [QUIETLY]
It's incredible.

02:09.477 --> 02:11.479
FIORE: Should have seen it
before the war.

02:13.568 --> 02:15.961
We told you about that.
The Endless War?

02:16.005 --> 02:17.615
Good and Evil.
Heaven and Hell.

02:17.659 --> 02:19.400
Meh.

02:19.443 --> 02:21.358
[WIND BLOWING]

02:21.402 --> 02:22.881
And it was always
tit for tat.

02:22.925 --> 02:24.361
We'd win a battle,
they'd win a battle,

02:28.365 --> 02:29.714
but nobody ever
really won or lost.

02:29.758 --> 02:31.368
Until God left.

02:34.937 --> 02:38.854
And now,
with Hell under
new management...

02:40.160 --> 02:41.509
I mean,
don't get me wrong.

02:41.552 --> 02:44.903
Jesus has been
doing his best,
but he's not Hitler.

02:44.947 --> 02:47.384
Doesn't really have
that killer instinct.

02:48.646 --> 02:51.214
Which brings us to you.

02:51.258 --> 02:55.349
We're just
so...glad you're here.

02:55.392 --> 02:58.221
♪♪

03:06.708 --> 03:08.623
[DOOR CLOSES]

03:27.729 --> 03:28.643
Cool.

03:33.125 --> 03:34.475
[WHISPERING]
What's going on?

03:34.518 --> 03:37.260
"What's going on?"
I've just been
telling you what!

03:37.304 --> 03:38.348
Well, you told me
"Jesus is no Hitler."

03:39.088 --> 03:41.308
Okay. Good to know.

03:41.351 --> 03:42.613
It's impossible.

03:42.657 --> 03:44.702
I feel like I'm
speaking monkey
to a cow.

03:46.138 --> 03:48.837
Right.
Heaven is empty.

03:48.880 --> 03:49.620
God is gone.

03:49.664 --> 03:51.883
We want you...

03:51.927 --> 03:53.842
[SNAPS FINGERS]

03:53.885 --> 03:56.410
[LIGHTS CLICK ON]

03:56.453 --> 03:58.716
...to take His place.

04:00.152 --> 04:02.372
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

04:38.582 --> 04:40.541
[PLANE ENGINE RUNNING]

04:40.584 --> 04:43.413
♪♪

04:45.850 --> 04:47.504
[TIRES SCREECH]

04:51.987 --> 04:54.468
[ENGINE REVS]

05:07.350 --> 05:08.917
[RADIO STATIC]

05:16.533 --> 05:18.318
[RADIO CLICKS OFF]

05:22.931 --> 05:24.324
[RADIO STATIC]

05:54.702 --> 05:56.878
[TIRES SCREECH]

05:56.921 --> 05:58.401
[ENGINE IDLING]

06:05.277 --> 06:08.019
[PAPER RUSTLES]

06:51.062 --> 06:52.760
[TULIP SIGHS]

06:57.155 --> 06:59.723
My dear.
You think maybe it...

06:59.767 --> 07:01.116
Back in a minute.

07:10.952 --> 07:12.867
[SIGHS]

07:12.910 --> 07:15.217
[CHICKENS CLUCK]

07:16.740 --> 07:19.003
♪♪

07:25.445 --> 07:27.925
ANNOUNCER: It's a bad day
on the oval for Brisbane.

07:27.969 --> 07:29.884
The undefeated Magpies extend their win streak to seven.

07:29.927 --> 07:32.974
Ugh, cheatin' bastards.
[DOORBELL RINGS]

07:33.017 --> 07:34.715
[CHEERS AND APPLAUSE]

07:47.031 --> 07:49.338
Evening.
Evening.

07:49.381 --> 07:51.949
The bell rung
and I didn't know
what to think.

07:51.993 --> 07:54.865
I mean,
out here at this hour,
and so forth.

07:54.909 --> 07:57.955
Is everything all right?
Me and my friend...

07:57.999 --> 08:00.001
We just had to
pull over at the side
of the road down there.

08:00.044 --> 08:02.090
Ah, I see.

08:02.133 --> 08:03.570
You're out of petrol,
are you?

08:03.613 --> 08:05.615
That what happened?
You're out of petrol?

08:07.530 --> 08:09.619
Yeah, of course.

08:09.663 --> 08:11.578
Come on in.
Let's get you
sorted out.

08:15.146 --> 08:17.975
Easy enough mistake
to make with the petrol.

08:18.019 --> 08:19.542
Done it myself last year.

08:19.586 --> 08:22.110
You thirsty?
I just fixed
a lemon squash.

08:29.204 --> 08:31.641
♪♪

08:33.034 --> 08:35.515
So, uh, yeah.

08:35.558 --> 08:38.605
I was halfway to Perth
before noticing

08:38.648 --> 08:40.781
the tank was as dry
as a nun's gusset.

08:41.956 --> 08:43.914
Oh, mate.

08:43.958 --> 08:45.525
I... I wish you wouldn't.

08:45.568 --> 08:47.178
Those towels
are the Missus'.

08:49.790 --> 08:51.139
Where is the Missus?

08:51.182 --> 08:53.315
With the Lord.

08:53.358 --> 08:55.012
Cancer.

08:55.056 --> 08:56.579
Hmm.

08:56.623 --> 08:58.450
With the Lord, huh?

08:58.494 --> 09:00.191
Good for her.

09:02.890 --> 09:05.196
Your arm.

09:05.240 --> 09:05.936
What happened?

09:06.894 --> 09:07.721
Sunburn.

09:12.856 --> 09:14.336
[GULPS]

09:14.379 --> 09:15.642
What do you want?

09:20.647 --> 09:21.822
Well.

09:23.519 --> 09:25.434
I came to eat your chickens.

09:26.043 --> 09:27.915
♪♪

09:45.976 --> 09:49.458
[DOG BARKS IN DISTANCE]

09:49.501 --> 09:50.938
[ECHOING] Hello?

09:54.071 --> 09:55.507
Nothing?

10:03.472 --> 10:05.866
♪♪

10:46.297 --> 10:47.472
He wasn't home?

10:49.300 --> 10:51.346
Nope.

10:51.389 --> 10:52.913
But I know
how to get Him.

10:58.309 --> 11:01.225
[ENGINE REVS]

11:01.269 --> 11:03.488
♪♪

11:06.013 --> 11:07.579
[LIVE A LITTLEPLAYING]

11:07.623 --> 11:08.755
[STEAM HISSES]

11:08.798 --> 11:11.192
♪ Give it up

11:11.235 --> 11:14.804
♪ Let's get the party started, never stop

11:14.848 --> 11:18.939
♪ You know a day
could never be the worst

11:18.982 --> 11:23.465
♪ Good times, so God, just live a little, live it up

11:23.508 --> 11:25.989
♪ Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah

11:26.033 --> 11:28.078
♪ Oh, oh, yeah

11:28.122 --> 11:32.169
♪ Everybody needs to let go
just for a while ♪

11:32.213 --> 11:33.257
Nothing for
the Allfather?

11:36.696 --> 11:39.133
The Allfather's business is
the business of the Allfather.

11:39.176 --> 11:40.743
Right.

11:43.224 --> 11:44.878
Guess he's still away.

11:44.921 --> 11:47.141
WOMAN: [ON PA]
Attention, Grail personnel.

11:47.184 --> 11:50.318
The modern miracles seminar

11:50.361 --> 11:53.582
will be held in conference room 6 at 10:00 a.m. Thursday.

11:53.625 --> 11:55.715
[DINGO BARKS]

11:59.196 --> 12:01.503
No! Stop!

12:02.678 --> 12:04.114
Stop!

12:06.334 --> 12:10.164
Stop! Please!

12:10.207 --> 12:11.818
Stop!

12:11.861 --> 12:13.384
[GROANS, SOBS]

12:13.428 --> 12:15.735
♪♪

12:29.139 --> 12:31.663
♪♪

12:36.016 --> 12:38.279
[INDISTINCT CONVERSATION]
Five, four, three...

12:38.322 --> 12:41.369
[CONVERSATION STOPS]

12:41.412 --> 12:44.198
Is your household cat hacking
into your bank account?

12:44.241 --> 12:45.982
We're gonna sit down
with an FBI agent

12:46.026 --> 12:48.071
with some
interesting thoughts,
but first,

12:48.115 --> 12:50.857
let's check-in with
the day's top news.

12:50.900 --> 12:52.075
Craig? Sounds like
Rosie O'Donnell's

12:52.119 --> 12:53.598
landed in hot water
again?

12:53.642 --> 12:55.252
Sorry, guys.
I'm not reading this crap.

12:55.296 --> 12:57.646
Not today.
[BOTH LAUGH]

12:57.689 --> 12:59.300
You know,
as a journalist,

12:59.343 --> 13:02.782
or what's left of one after
six years on this show,

13:02.825 --> 13:05.610
I feel bound to talk
about the darkening
political situation.

13:06.611 --> 13:08.483
Australia
and New Zealand.

13:08.526 --> 13:10.790
Ah, this explosion
thing, right?
In the Outback?

13:10.833 --> 13:14.097
Yeah. This 25-kiloton
detonation

13:14.141 --> 13:16.883
pushing the world's
superpowers
to take sides

13:16.926 --> 13:20.234
and so threaten
a wider nuclear exchange

13:20.277 --> 13:23.628
that will leave the planet
an ash-choked shitscape.

13:23.672 --> 13:25.369
[CHUCKLING]
Scary stuff.

13:25.413 --> 13:26.980
Maybe we should
break for commercial?

13:27.023 --> 13:27.807
FEMALE ANCHOR:
[CHUCKLING] Craig.

13:27.850 --> 13:29.591
There are children
watching.

13:29.634 --> 13:32.289
Well, then the children
can tell their parents

13:32.333 --> 13:35.292
to get on their knees
and beg for God's mercy.

13:35.336 --> 13:36.903
Because
as far as I can see,

13:36.946 --> 13:38.078
the only thing
that will save us

13:38.121 --> 13:39.906
is a goddamn miracle!

13:39.949 --> 13:41.429
♪♪

13:48.262 --> 13:50.699
Go on. Sit.

13:50.742 --> 13:54.268
Someone
needs to step in.

13:54.311 --> 13:55.660
Why not you?

14:15.071 --> 14:18.074
[ECHOING]
I am the alpha

14:18.118 --> 14:20.772
and the omega!

14:20.816 --> 14:24.037
I am the bright morning star.

14:24.080 --> 14:25.995
♪♪

14:43.491 --> 14:44.971
[NORMAL VOICE] No.

14:47.930 --> 14:49.410
I won't do it.

14:49.453 --> 14:52.979
That is a natural
first response
to what would be

14:53.022 --> 14:55.285
a big lifestyle change.
And...

14:55.329 --> 14:58.332
It's not a lifestyle change.
It's a sin.

14:58.375 --> 15:00.160
Well, it's not ideal.

15:00.203 --> 15:03.641
But "sin"'s a bit strong.
Sin's a bit...

15:03.685 --> 15:05.208
It's the worst sin there is!
You're all traitors!

15:05.252 --> 15:06.862
[SWORDS UNSHEATHE]

15:06.906 --> 15:07.950
Stop! Stop!
Stop! Stop! Stop.

15:09.386 --> 15:12.085
We have got
to stick together!

15:12.128 --> 15:14.696
There'll be plenty
of time for fighting
when Hell arrives.

15:20.006 --> 15:22.312
[FOGHORN BLOWS]

15:22.356 --> 15:24.097
♪ Just an average guy

15:26.795 --> 15:30.755
♪ With a yearning I can't deny

15:32.235 --> 15:34.498
♪ Don't suppose
you could fall for

15:35.717 --> 15:38.111
♪ Someone like me ♪

15:38.154 --> 15:40.591
I've always...
I've always wondered
about that.

15:40.635 --> 15:42.985
And... And the...
The big one...
It's furry.

15:43.029 --> 15:44.552
It looks like a...

15:44.595 --> 15:46.641
Like a thick-crusted
beaver pizza.

15:46.684 --> 15:48.164
It's called a "shtremiel."

15:48.208 --> 15:49.861
Worn over the kippah.

15:49.905 --> 15:52.429
Connotes an extra level
of devotion.

15:52.473 --> 15:53.996
Yes? Good?

15:54.040 --> 15:56.042
Excellent. Thank you.
Got it.

15:56.085 --> 15:57.695
Is that why
you've come,

15:57.739 --> 16:00.220
for my knowledge
of traditional Jewish hats
and headwear?

16:00.263 --> 16:02.439
You know
what we want,
Dany.

16:03.832 --> 16:04.833
Right.

16:05.312 --> 16:07.009
♪♪

16:07.053 --> 16:08.445
Who we want.

16:09.620 --> 16:11.013
But first...

16:12.884 --> 16:14.103
You know what I want.

16:15.278 --> 16:17.150
♪♪

16:20.631 --> 16:23.547
[HORNS HONKING]

16:23.591 --> 16:25.854
[INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS]

16:25.897 --> 16:27.856
MAN: Order up.
[BELL DINGS]

16:27.899 --> 16:31.120
Honestly,
I don't know why
I ever left this town.

16:31.164 --> 16:33.340
It's got good food.

16:33.383 --> 16:34.471
Pubs never close.

16:36.256 --> 16:38.345
Actually,
do you know what?

16:38.388 --> 16:40.434
I should go down
and see the boys
at McSorley's.

16:40.477 --> 16:43.089
Of course,
they won't be boys
anymore, will they?

16:43.132 --> 16:45.004
They were like
20-something
then, so...

16:48.659 --> 16:50.313
Well, Christ,
they'd be dead now,
wouldn't they?

16:50.357 --> 16:52.228
Yeah. Probably.

16:59.583 --> 17:03.022
Look, this thing...
That she's asking you for?

17:05.937 --> 17:07.156
I can do that
if you want.

17:09.158 --> 17:10.551
Everything good
for you two?

17:10.594 --> 17:13.510
Oh, it's great.
Thank you so much.
It was lovely.

17:13.554 --> 17:14.946
[PAPER TEARS]

17:17.471 --> 17:19.168
And just say it.
Say the word,
and I'll do it.

17:23.564 --> 17:25.696
You know, I don't like it
either, all right?

17:25.740 --> 17:27.524
But the gloves
are off now.

17:27.568 --> 17:29.439
We tried to be nice.

17:29.483 --> 17:31.137
We tried to play it
by the book.

17:31.180 --> 17:32.964
Where did it get us?

17:33.008 --> 17:36.577
Guilt and just feeling bad
about every goddamn thing.

17:36.620 --> 17:37.317
Well, screw that.

17:40.711 --> 17:42.539
The gloves are off.

17:43.932 --> 17:45.368
They're all the way off.

17:52.114 --> 17:54.160
[GUNSHOTS]
[SCREAMING]

17:54.203 --> 17:56.423
♪♪

18:19.620 --> 18:22.666
[GROANING]

18:27.367 --> 18:28.498
My child.

18:28.542 --> 18:30.326
[GROANS]

18:30.370 --> 18:31.675
Whoa! Whoa!

18:31.719 --> 18:33.503
So?

18:33.547 --> 18:37.290
Apart from the erection,
what do you think of him?

18:38.378 --> 18:39.553
He's, uh...

18:39.596 --> 18:40.815
HITLER:
Hold that thought.

18:42.860 --> 18:44.775
[CRACKS KNUCKLES, GRUNTS]

18:46.647 --> 18:48.344
[PLAYS THAT OLD SOFT SHOE]

18:52.000 --> 18:54.872
[LAUGHS]

18:54.916 --> 18:57.571
♪♪

19:05.709 --> 19:08.059
Wait,
I thought the Messiah
was supposed to be

19:08.103 --> 19:09.887
a [QUIETLY]
good dancer?

19:09.931 --> 19:11.280
[GUNSHOTS]
Whoa! Whoa!

19:12.847 --> 19:15.241
Jesus Christ!

19:15.284 --> 19:18.461
[SIGHS]
That's not
the Messiah.

19:18.505 --> 19:19.375
You...
You killed him!

19:20.246 --> 19:22.117
Just a clone.

19:22.161 --> 19:23.684
There are
hundreds of them,

19:23.727 --> 19:26.774
running around
like dumb monkeys.

19:26.817 --> 19:29.777
That... That's no
monkey, Hitler.

19:30.604 --> 19:32.258
But the real Messiah?

19:32.301 --> 19:35.739
The one they need
to end the world?

19:35.783 --> 19:37.480
They have lost him.

19:37.524 --> 19:39.221
He is gone.

19:39.265 --> 19:40.831
Disappeared.

19:40.875 --> 19:42.703
And no one
knows where.

19:42.746 --> 19:44.313
Except you,
of course.

19:44.966 --> 19:46.663
I don't know either.

19:46.707 --> 19:50.841
Hit by a bus,
stumbled into
a wood chipper.

19:51.407 --> 19:52.452
Who knows?

19:54.410 --> 19:56.847
But more importantly,
who cares?

19:58.501 --> 20:02.375
When we have
a perfectly good Messiah?

20:02.418 --> 20:04.507
A deserving Messiah,

20:04.551 --> 20:06.901
all ready to go?

20:06.944 --> 20:08.946
Hm?

20:08.990 --> 20:10.383
What are you
talking about?

20:11.471 --> 20:13.603
Jesus.

20:13.647 --> 20:16.606
I'm talking about you.

20:16.650 --> 20:19.348
♪♪

20:22.830 --> 20:24.484
Okay.

20:24.527 --> 20:26.050
All right.

20:26.094 --> 20:27.574
Yeah.

20:30.054 --> 20:31.404
[CELL PHONE BEEPS]

20:38.149 --> 20:39.716
You killed my husband.

20:39.760 --> 20:42.502
Like you asked
me to, Dany.No, I know, I know.

20:42.545 --> 20:44.068
Like you've been asking me
for 10 years, Dany.

20:44.112 --> 20:45.548
I know, I know.

20:45.592 --> 20:47.898
Look. You got what you want,
now we get what we want.

20:47.942 --> 20:49.422
No, I know, I know.

20:50.988 --> 20:53.121
I didn't think
you'd do it!

20:53.164 --> 20:54.905
What?
You always said no.

20:54.949 --> 20:57.299
100 times I asked you
and you always said no.

20:57.343 --> 20:58.474
[QUIETLY] Seriously?

20:58.518 --> 20:59.736
Look, you g...
Shut up!

20:59.780 --> 21:01.390
Who is this person?

21:01.956 --> 21:03.740
Where is he?

21:03.784 --> 21:06.656
Here's the thing.
Jesse gave him
to me for safekeeping.

21:06.700 --> 21:08.658
There's no "thing," Dany.
We had a deal.

21:08.702 --> 21:09.964
Where is he?

21:12.271 --> 21:14.360
You don't understand.

21:14.403 --> 21:17.928
What you are asking...
I can't do it.

21:17.972 --> 21:20.017
I can't take you to him.

21:20.061 --> 21:22.368
I'm sorry.
Oh, bullshit.

21:22.411 --> 21:24.892
You're right.
I misspoke.

21:24.935 --> 21:27.155
I'm not sorry.

21:27.198 --> 21:28.548
And I won't do it.

21:28.591 --> 21:30.114
[GASPS]

21:30.158 --> 21:32.900
♪♪

21:32.943 --> 21:34.423
[GRUNTS]

21:38.514 --> 21:40.255
Where is he?

21:40.299 --> 21:42.301
♪♪

21:55.401 --> 21:57.272
FIORE: Sorry.

21:57.316 --> 22:01.189
It's just... We're trying to
think outside the box.

22:05.411 --> 22:07.587
I can't believe
I'm dead and I still
want a cigarette.

22:15.551 --> 22:17.466
Nasty habit.

22:21.688 --> 22:23.733
But it keeps me off
the speedballs.

22:25.822 --> 22:28.259
How is that Cassidy
anyway?

22:29.696 --> 22:30.697
Alive.

22:30.740 --> 22:32.133
[CHUCKLES]

22:32.176 --> 22:33.526
Yeah.

22:33.569 --> 22:35.136
He is that.

22:35.179 --> 22:37.268
Look.

22:37.312 --> 22:38.792
You don't want
to go against
God's law?

22:40.097 --> 22:42.448
I respect that.

22:42.491 --> 22:46.234
But what if
by refusing the throne,

22:46.277 --> 22:48.410
you're going against
His will?

22:48.454 --> 22:52.893
I mean,
He did send you
here, huh?

22:52.936 --> 22:54.155
But why?

22:54.198 --> 22:57.201
I cheated, I stole.

22:57.245 --> 22:58.855
I-I killed people.

23:00.509 --> 23:03.382
I mean, some had it coming,
but some didn't.

23:06.123 --> 23:08.648
There was this kid once
in Dallas, a bank teller.

23:11.128 --> 23:12.478
He just got in my way.

23:14.523 --> 23:16.438
Why am I
telling you this?

23:16.482 --> 23:18.919
You done
some bad things,

23:18.962 --> 23:21.443
but you done
good things, too.

23:21.487 --> 23:24.446
In the end, who gets into
Heaven, who goes to Hell?

23:24.490 --> 23:26.535
It's complicated.

23:27.493 --> 23:29.320
My only two friends.

23:30.931 --> 23:33.716
Two friends.

23:33.760 --> 23:35.326
They let me down,
but not in any big way.

23:35.370 --> 23:37.894
I mean, [QUIETLY]
it was in a big way,

23:37.938 --> 23:39.330
[NORMAL VOICE] but I'm sure
they didn't mean it.

23:42.508 --> 23:44.031
I had to get away
from them, too.

23:45.728 --> 23:47.556
I was afraid
I was gonna kill them.

23:49.645 --> 23:51.386
You see, with all that
hate in my heart,

23:51.430 --> 23:52.431
why would He
send me here?

23:54.998 --> 23:57.479
Because He knows
you forgave them.

23:58.045 --> 23:59.829
I haven't.

24:01.004 --> 24:03.833
♪♪

24:10.187 --> 24:11.711
It's because...

24:12.929 --> 24:14.496
This isn't Heaven.

24:15.323 --> 24:17.151
♪♪

24:18.152 --> 24:19.370
Is it, Fiore?

24:20.110 --> 24:21.503
I never said it was.

24:22.330 --> 24:24.027
[MACHINE POWERS DOWN]

24:27.248 --> 24:29.859
[DISTANT SCREAMING]

24:29.903 --> 24:32.253
♪♪

24:37.084 --> 24:39.086
[BANGS ON DOOR]

24:39.129 --> 24:39.956
Get me out of here!

24:42.742 --> 24:43.917
[ECHOING] Get me out of here!

24:45.788 --> 24:47.355
Get me out of here!

24:47.398 --> 24:48.530
Get me out of here!

24:52.491 --> 24:53.753
In there?

24:54.928 --> 24:56.582
You can't do this.

24:58.975 --> 25:00.194
Show us.

25:00.237 --> 25:02.718
Or what?
You gonna shoot me, too?

25:02.762 --> 25:03.850
Yeah.

25:05.547 --> 25:07.375
What happened to you?

25:07.418 --> 25:08.985
♪♪

25:09.769 --> 25:10.770
Where's Jesse?

25:12.511 --> 25:13.990
Tulip?
Where is...

25:14.034 --> 25:14.991
He's dead.

25:16.515 --> 25:17.690
Show us.

25:23.173 --> 25:24.914
HITLER: Nein,
there is neintime
for this now.

25:24.958 --> 25:27.177
JESUS: Agree
to disagree,
Adolf, okay?

25:27.221 --> 25:28.396
Nein!There
is only disagree

25:28.439 --> 25:30.572
because you are
the Messiah.

25:30.616 --> 25:33.444
I have waited too long
to have my plans come
crashing down now!

25:33.488 --> 25:35.490
Hey, hey, hey,
I don't respond
well to yelling.

25:35.534 --> 25:36.535
HITLER: Where are
you going now?

25:39.886 --> 25:41.104
Fine!

25:41.148 --> 25:44.499
You go.
Pray on it.

25:44.543 --> 25:48.285
You shall not muzzle an ox
when it treads out the grain.

25:48.329 --> 25:50.418
[SCOFFS] What does
that even mean?

25:52.376 --> 25:53.987
Your latte,
my Lord.

25:55.597 --> 25:56.555
Bless you, Hoover Two.

26:04.954 --> 26:06.173
Sugar!

26:06.216 --> 26:07.304
Already in there.

26:07.348 --> 26:08.349
Two packets.

26:15.922 --> 26:18.185
♪♪

26:20.491 --> 26:24.234
Bar'chu et Hashem
ham'vorach.

26:24.278 --> 26:27.455
CONGREGATION: Baruch Hashem
ham'vorach l'olam vaed.

26:27.498 --> 26:30.589
[CHANTING IN HEBREW]

26:37.552 --> 26:41.817
[CONGREGATION CHANTS
IN HEBREW]

26:42.949 --> 26:44.341
[WHISPERING] Well,
where is he?

26:44.385 --> 26:45.734
[SIGHS]

26:45.778 --> 26:47.431
[WHISPERING] I hope
he melts your faces off.

26:47.475 --> 26:50.304
[CHANTING CONTINUES]

26:55.483 --> 26:58.399
♪♪

27:12.065 --> 27:13.806
Are you ready?

27:13.849 --> 27:15.590
No. We need a minute
to catch our breath.

27:15.634 --> 27:17.113
Open the goddamn door,
Dany.

27:36.350 --> 27:39.919
Uh, bak-too.
[LAUGHS]

27:42.095 --> 27:43.139
Jesus.

27:43.183 --> 27:44.880
I-I get it.

27:44.924 --> 27:48.014
When Jesse
first sent him to me
for safekeeping,

27:48.057 --> 27:52.366
I thought,
"This is God's
chosen one?

27:52.409 --> 27:54.063
"He's raping
blocks of cheese."

27:55.325 --> 27:56.457
But then...

27:58.415 --> 28:00.113
Something happened.

28:00.156 --> 28:04.334
[GROANS]
His power,
his love changed me.

28:04.378 --> 28:07.250
It changed all of us.

28:07.294 --> 28:09.688
[MUMBLES]

28:10.210 --> 28:11.690
Watch.

28:13.430 --> 28:15.868
[PLAYS OLD SOFT SHOE]

28:15.911 --> 28:18.131
♪♪

28:23.049 --> 28:25.007
[SHOES TAPPING]

28:25.051 --> 28:27.314
[LAUGHS]

28:28.271 --> 28:30.621
♪♪

28:43.112 --> 28:45.071
[LAUGHS]

28:46.463 --> 28:48.770
[MOANS HAPPILY]

28:54.950 --> 28:58.911
Do you understand now
how special he really is?

29:00.173 --> 29:02.784
Why I could never
let you take him.

29:03.306 --> 29:04.743
♪♪

29:04.786 --> 29:06.092
Ever.

29:07.833 --> 29:09.660
[GRUNTS]

29:14.317 --> 29:15.623
Bye-bye!

29:23.674 --> 29:25.459
DANY: Stop them!

29:25.502 --> 29:26.765
They're taking
our Messiah!

29:28.201 --> 29:31.987
CONGREGATION:
[CHANTING] Moshiach!
Moshiach!

29:32.031 --> 29:34.903
[CHANTING CONTINUES]

29:35.643 --> 29:37.863
[HUMPERDOO GRUNTING]

29:54.880 --> 29:55.837
[SNARLS]

29:57.404 --> 30:00.059
Muhh roooo ahh!

30:00.624 --> 30:02.409
[MUMBLING]

30:09.372 --> 30:11.635
[LAUGHS HAPPILY]

30:18.033 --> 30:19.034
Bye-bye.

30:22.951 --> 30:24.431
[LAUGHS]

30:30.741 --> 30:33.222
[HUMMING]

30:33.266 --> 30:34.441
Where are you
taking Him?

30:34.484 --> 30:35.877
HUMPERDOO: Moshiach.
DANY: Answer me!

30:37.313 --> 30:38.488
Where are you
taking Him?

30:38.532 --> 30:42.057
[DOOR CLOSES]

30:44.407 --> 30:46.322
Betsy Cullen.

30:46.366 --> 30:48.324
Betsy Cullen... She lived
down the road from me

30:48.368 --> 30:50.457
when I was just a lad
in Dublin.

30:50.500 --> 30:52.633
There was Betsy,
her husband.

30:52.676 --> 30:55.505
She had six sons,
and they were
good Catholics, you know.

30:55.549 --> 30:58.726
Devoted. They loved God.

30:58.769 --> 31:00.119
And then the
war came along,

31:00.162 --> 31:01.816
and one Cullen boy
after another,

31:01.860 --> 31:03.949
he come back from France
in a box, see?

31:03.992 --> 31:06.690
It was Betsy's husband,
five sons.

31:06.734 --> 31:09.171
All dead.
Which left Bobby.

31:09.215 --> 31:11.260
He was like the fair-haired
favorite, you know.

31:11.304 --> 31:16.352
Only Bobby... He died, too,
at his daddy's wake.

31:16.396 --> 31:18.311
He stepped out the bar,
he walked into the road,

31:18.354 --> 31:20.182
he got hit by
a cement truck.

31:20.226 --> 31:22.358
And do you know
what happened
to Betsy Cullen

31:22.402 --> 31:25.535
and her devotions
as a result of her
many sorrows?

31:25.579 --> 31:26.754
Do you know?

31:29.017 --> 31:30.758
Absolutely nothing.

31:32.455 --> 31:34.980
She still loved God.

31:35.023 --> 31:37.983
Because
she was an idiot.

31:38.026 --> 31:40.768
[CONGREGATION MURMURS ANGRILY]
She was a sucker,
as are all of you.

31:40.811 --> 31:42.813
And in answer
to your question,

31:42.857 --> 31:44.293
we heard
that your Lord...

31:44.337 --> 31:46.643
He loves your Messiah,
too.

31:46.687 --> 31:48.297
So we're going to
kill him...

31:48.341 --> 31:51.387
[MURMURING CONTINUES]

31:51.431 --> 31:53.563
[LAUGHS] And we're going to
make God watch, all right?

31:53.607 --> 31:56.131
♪♪

31:57.916 --> 32:00.919
[DOOR OPENS, CLOSES]

32:00.962 --> 32:03.399
I didn't even know
we had a Messiah.

32:03.443 --> 32:05.314
Because we didn't
tell you, Eli!

32:06.576 --> 32:07.708
Schmuck.

32:11.451 --> 32:14.106
[POLICE RADIO CHATTER]

32:14.149 --> 32:16.847
♪♪

32:18.023 --> 32:20.373
[TELEPHONE RINGS]

32:20.416 --> 32:22.418
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

32:22.462 --> 32:23.637
Got a call for you,
Chief.

32:23.680 --> 32:25.682
I get 30 minutes
for lunch.

32:25.726 --> 32:27.423
I got 27 more to go.

32:27.467 --> 32:29.164
Chief,
it's long-distance.

32:30.078 --> 32:33.212
♪♪

32:36.432 --> 32:37.520
Wittman here.

32:37.564 --> 32:39.609
Chief. It's Nix.

32:39.653 --> 32:41.960
It's been 14 months.
I thought you were dead.

32:42.003 --> 32:44.266
No, sir.
I'm alive and well

32:44.310 --> 32:46.312
and I'm holding
all the evidence I need

32:46.355 --> 32:49.489
to stop these Grail bastards
in their tracks.

32:49.532 --> 32:51.621
You're saying that this is
more than phony car tags?

32:51.665 --> 32:53.449
It's a global conspiracy.

32:53.493 --> 32:55.016
Hitler and Jesus,

32:55.060 --> 32:56.452
they're taking orders
from this,

32:56.496 --> 32:58.889
this mutilated maniac

32:58.933 --> 33:00.848
who wants to set off
a nuclear war

33:00.891 --> 33:02.241
with a tap-dancing imbecile.

33:02.284 --> 33:04.808
Christ, Nix.

33:04.852 --> 33:07.072
If what you're saying
is true,

33:07.115 --> 33:08.682
you'll make detective
before you're 30.

33:08.725 --> 33:10.292
I didn't get into this
for promotions.

33:10.336 --> 33:12.947
I'm just a cop
doing his job
to keep people safe.

33:12.991 --> 33:15.167
As long as I got a badge
in my wallet,

33:15.210 --> 33:17.865
there isn't going to be
any damn apocalypse.

33:17.908 --> 33:20.694
[SCOFFS] No, sir.
Not on my...

33:20.737 --> 33:22.783
[SILENCED GUNSHOT]
[CELL PHONE CLATTERS]

33:23.653 --> 33:24.785
Nix?

33:26.047 --> 33:28.006
♪♪

33:44.370 --> 33:46.111
[LAUGHS HAPPILY]

33:48.896 --> 33:51.116
Yay!

33:51.638 --> 33:53.727
Huppa-doo!

33:55.120 --> 33:57.513
Yay!

33:57.557 --> 33:58.862
[LAUGHS]

34:07.654 --> 34:10.178
♪♪

34:15.923 --> 34:18.969
YOUNG JESSE:
I did it, Daddy!
I prayed for this!

34:19.013 --> 34:19.883
It's all my fault!
[GUNSHOT]

34:19.927 --> 34:22.495
[MACHINE POWERS DOWN]

34:22.538 --> 34:24.975
♪♪

34:30.503 --> 34:31.634
Give me a break.

34:41.296 --> 34:42.906
Hello again.

34:42.950 --> 34:44.125
What are you doing here?

34:45.953 --> 34:47.955
You're supposed to
be an angel.

34:47.998 --> 34:49.609
It's a long story.

34:49.652 --> 34:51.219
But suffice to say,

34:51.263 --> 34:53.178
when you've got a grand-a-day
speedball habit,

34:53.221 --> 34:55.180
Heaven's a challenge.

34:56.398 --> 34:59.314
But this...
You're just...

34:59.358 --> 35:01.751
I'm just a projection.

35:01.795 --> 35:05.103
This isn't Heaven and that is
not the Lord's throne.

35:05.146 --> 35:07.975
But the offer
is real.

35:08.454 --> 35:10.586
♪♪

35:16.157 --> 35:19.987
You take it
and we'll set you free.

35:20.030 --> 35:22.729
[QUIETLY] Just because
I've got issues with God

35:22.772 --> 35:25.514
doesn't mean I'm going
to listen to some
bird-faced dope fiend

35:25.558 --> 35:26.994
about replacing Him.

35:31.259 --> 35:33.131
Okay, let's try
something else,
then.

35:33.174 --> 35:35.394
♪♪

35:43.358 --> 35:45.360
What is this?

35:45.404 --> 35:46.970
This is Heaven.

35:47.014 --> 35:49.625
In 2015.

35:49.669 --> 35:51.366
Watch and listen.

35:52.150 --> 35:54.543
♪♪

35:54.587 --> 35:57.198
YOUNG MAN: Aw, c'mon, God!
Not summer school.

35:57.242 --> 35:59.069
No.
[TAPE FAST-FORWARDS]

35:59.113 --> 36:01.202
MAN: God, I beg of you,
in all your glory.

36:01.246 --> 36:02.725
If you clear up
this rash,

36:02.769 --> 36:04.684
I'll never look at
another hooker again.

36:04.727 --> 36:06.425
No.
[TAPE FAST-FORWARDS]

36:06.468 --> 36:07.817
WOMAN: Lord, please,
let it be benign.

36:07.861 --> 36:09.689
[SIGHS]

36:09.732 --> 36:10.994
[DOOR OPENS]

36:12.213 --> 36:15.216
♪♪

36:31.101 --> 36:33.365
My Lord, I bring, erm...

36:35.541 --> 36:37.630
Difficult news.

36:37.673 --> 36:40.241
Genesis has escaped.

36:40.285 --> 36:43.113
♪♪

36:43.157 --> 36:45.812
We're not sure
how or where.

36:45.855 --> 36:47.205
I see.

36:47.248 --> 36:48.858
I'm really sorry.

36:48.902 --> 36:51.252
You entrusted it to
our safekeeping and...

36:51.296 --> 36:54.473
L-L-Let me just, um...

37:00.566 --> 37:02.132
Shit.

37:03.221 --> 37:04.526
FIORE: We'll get it back.

37:04.570 --> 37:06.354
Deblanch and I
will go down there,

37:06.398 --> 37:07.660
and we'll find it,
and... And...

37:07.703 --> 37:10.663
Thank you for
telling me, my son.

37:10.706 --> 37:15.233
Now, uh, if you would
leave me with my thoughts,

37:15.276 --> 37:18.758
I will come up
with a solution.

37:18.801 --> 37:20.890
Yes, my Lord.

37:20.934 --> 37:22.501
Of course.

37:23.502 --> 37:25.460
♪♪

37:32.989 --> 37:34.556
[GLASS SHATTERS]

37:34.600 --> 37:36.515
♪♪

37:36.558 --> 37:37.429
My Lord?

37:44.697 --> 37:45.959
What the...

37:46.002 --> 37:49.049
[HOLIDAY ROADPLAYING]

37:49.092 --> 37:53.880
♪ I found out long ago

37:53.923 --> 37:57.405
♪ It's a long way down
the holiday road

37:58.972 --> 38:03.977
♪ Holiday road

38:04.020 --> 38:08.808
♪ Holiday road

38:08.851 --> 38:12.377
♪♪

38:12.420 --> 38:17.425
♪ Jack be nimble,
Jack be quick

38:17.469 --> 38:21.821
♪ Take a ride on
the West Coast kick

38:21.864 --> 38:27.043
♪ Holiday road

38:27.087 --> 38:31.961
♪ Holiday road

38:32.005 --> 38:37.053
♪ Holiday road

38:37.097 --> 38:42.276
♪ Holiday road

38:42.320 --> 38:45.366
♪♪

38:54.332 --> 38:57.204
♪ I found out long ago ♪

38:57.247 --> 38:59.554
♪♪

39:06.344 --> 39:08.258
The dog suit's
a bit weird.

39:08.302 --> 39:09.912
The dog suit
is disgusting.

39:14.264 --> 39:15.831
That can't be
all He's doing.

39:17.703 --> 39:19.269
He must have
some bigger plan.

39:20.401 --> 39:22.447
Oh, you're right
about that.

39:22.490 --> 39:23.622
He's got a big plan.

39:23.665 --> 39:25.493
[SEWING MACHINE CLICKING]

39:27.147 --> 39:30.803
And he's been hard at it
for months now.

39:30.846 --> 39:32.326
Tinkering,

39:32.370 --> 39:33.501
experimenting...

39:34.241 --> 39:36.548
♪♪

39:38.158 --> 39:40.203
First, he made dinosaurs.

39:40.247 --> 39:41.640
Then he created man.

39:41.683 --> 39:42.597
And now...

39:43.293 --> 39:44.773
[BLOOD SQUIRTS]

39:44.817 --> 39:47.428
♪♪

39:51.040 --> 39:52.955
His Great Design.

39:52.999 --> 39:55.436
Creation Part Three.

39:57.873 --> 39:59.440
God's going to replace us.

40:02.487 --> 40:04.097
Unless...

40:04.532 --> 40:06.752
♪♪

40:15.238 --> 40:17.240
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]
